Here you can add different display drivers if you need to use a different type 
or model of screen.
For it to work correctly with the entire system, use the touch and display 
interfaces located in the interface folder of their respective module.

If your screen has built-in touch functionality, such as the ILI9341, and the library 
supports it, you can use it directly in your driver class with `getTouch`, implementing 
both interfaces with the same library. If your library doesn't support it and you have to 
use a secondary library, you can always create a specific class for touch in the driver 
folder of its respective module.


====== Display ======

|--src
   |-- app
   |-- communication
   |-- display
      |--drivers
      |--interface
         |- idisplay_driver.h

====== Display ======

|--src
   |-- app
   |-- communication
   |-- touch
      |--drivers
      |--interface
         |- itouch_driver.h

